org.anyframe.idgen.impl.strategy
Class MixStrategy

All Implemented Interfaces:
IdGenStrategy
public class MixStrategy
extends AbstractStrategy

MixStrategy is a kind of id generation strategy. MixStrategy assembles prefix, suffix, original string, paddingChar, maxCiphers into new id. For example,
prefix is a 'TEST-'
paddingChar is a '0'
original string is a '12'
and maxCiphers is a 5
in result, new id is a 'TEST-00012'. * The Configuration to use a MixStrategy looks like the following: 

  <property name="prefix" value="TEST-"/>
  <property name="suffix" value="-TEST"/>     
  <property name="maxCiphers" value="5"/>
  <property name="paddingChar" value="0"/>

Author:
Jonghwan Jeong
